  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate an intervention to prevent complications after
      pancreas surgery. The goal is to determine if placing a stent into the pancreatic duct before
      surgery will decrease or prevent leaking from the pancreatic duct after surgery. Leaks are
      common after pancreas surgery and can result in serious problems and post-operative pain. The
      study will compare two groups. One group will have the stent before surgery, and the other
      group will have standard pancreas surgery, no endoscopy, and no stent.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
